claim:journal-as-distribution-in-decline  a fair2r:Claim ;
    rdfs:label "Traditional publishing is under stress; the journal-as-distribution concept (which pre-dates the internet by three centuries) is being weakened by preprint servers, overlay journals, registered reports, and artefact-versioned repositories; LLM-generated submissions tip a slow drift into a visible crisis. F(AI)^2R is designed to fit both the legacy and the emerging scholarly-communication ecosystem."@en ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo agent:human-author ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom  src:eisen2018preprints , src:tennant2016open , src:conroy2023sleuths ;
    fair2r:verificationState verif:human-confirmed ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date .

