hc:fix-beamer-conference-build-attempt-2  a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Second attempt at fixing the conference-deck Beamer compile: log-dump-on-failure + replace inline TikZ"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "corrective-intervention" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "medium" ;
    rdfs:comment "Attempt 1 (PR #21 first commit) failed CI as well. Two changes: (1) build-slides.yml now runs latex-action with continue_on_error=true and adds an `if: failure()` step that tails the .log file into the workflow output; the next failure will show actual LaTeX error lines without auth. (2) The two inline TikZ figures in conference-30min.tex (ten-stage pipeline, verification ladder) are replaced with simpler tabular and framed-text layouts; TikZ is the most likely culprit and removing it restores a compilable deck while we wait for the log to confirm. Pitch deck unchanged."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-07"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:workflow-build-slides ,
                    ent:slidedeck-conference .

hc:pages-staleness-fix       a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher report: the deployed Pages site does not seem up to date"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "corrective-intervention" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "low" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher reported the Pages site appears stale after PR #19. Sandbox cannot fetch the live URL to confirm. Three defensive fixes: (1) scripts/build_provenance_site.py now writes _site/.nojekyll so GitHub Pages does not run Jekyll on the artefact (Jekyll can misbehave on the static/ tree); (2) the page template's hero section gains a visible build-tag printing the cache-bust hash, so the researcher can confirm at a glance which bundle their browser is rendering; (3) touching scripts/build_provenance_site.py and site/static/style.css matches pages.yml's path filter, so the merge triggers a fresh pages.yml run and forces the CDN cache (max-age=600) to refresh."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:script-build-provenance-site .

hc:beamer-only-slides        a fair2r:HumanContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Researcher decision: only ship Beamer (drop Marp); equivalent Beamer is OK as well"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "structural-decision" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    rdfs:comment "After the Marp asset-inlining fix landed (PR #18), the researcher decided 'only ship beamer'. Beamer reuses the existing LaTeX toolchain (xu-cheng/latex-action), the DLR colours from paper/style/fair2r.sty, and the same TikZ idiom as the paper figures; no Chromium / Node / Marp / theme-inlining preprocessor. New slides/style/fair2r-beamer.sty is the slide companion to paper/style/fair2r.sty (mid-grey frame titles, DLR-Blue accent rule, hairline rules, the \\sectiondivider helper). Both decks rewritten in Beamer; slides/Makefile and the build-slides workflow now use latexmk + xu-cheng/latex-action mirroring paper/Makefile and build-paper.yml. README and site/index.md updated to point at the Beamer PDFs only (no PPTX); CLAUDE.md and doc/methodology.md primary-artefact list updated to .tex sources; agents/presentation.md rewritten as Beamer-only with explicit refusal to reintroduce a Marp / HTML / PPTX path."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date ;
    prov:influenced ent:slide-style ,
