hc:obs-coding-structure        a fair2r:MetaContribution ;
    rdfs:label "Coding with LLMs: structure becomes more important; visions, feature sets, dependencies are the human's load (the coding-counterpart of the writing partition); domain vocabulary fluency is a collaboration multiplier"@en ;
    fair2r:contributedBy agent:human-author ;
    fair2r:contributionType "observation" ;
    fair2r:contributionLeverage "high" ;
    fair2r:promotedToPaper "pending" ;
    rdfs:comment "Researcher observed during the slide-decks session: 'In coding with LLMs somehow structure becomes more important, like guiding and shaping a river of code --- it's more about visions, feature sets, dependencies.' Extended in the next message: 'addition to the river thought, as a dev / cs engineer i have the vocabulary to effectively work with the llm by referring to things more specifically producing a more general cohesiveness'. The model identified this as the coding-counterpart of the writing partition (same partition, same coupling rule, same diagnostic). The vocabulary-fluency extension adds a second layer to the equity discussion in §sustainability: it is not just access to frontier models that is asymmetric, it is access to the formal vocabulary that makes the cooperation effective. Researchers from disciplines with rich shared formal vocabularies (CS, mathematics, physics, well-formalised parts of biology) start with an advantage that does not transfer to disciplines whose vocabularies are still being built. The eight integrated practices of F(AI)^2R are themselves a vocabulary for cooperative writing; the act of naming them gives a future researcher a set of API terms to reach for. The paper's contribution, on this reading, is partly the practices and partly the vocabulary that lets a researcher operate them precisely."@en ;
    dcterms:created "2026-05-06"^^xsd:date .

